Hi, Paige.

As paige wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/25/2004 at 20:55:26 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>I have 4 hundreds. I have 3 more ones than tens.  My digits make a 
>sum of 9.  what number am I?
>
>[Difficulty]
>the my digits make a sum of 9.
>
>[Thoughts]
>400+10+3=413

You've got the right number of hundreds. You don't have 3 more ones 
than tens: you have 1 ten and 3 ones, and 3 isn't 3 more than 1. And 
your digits don't make a sum of 9: 4+1+3 = 8, not 9. But you're 
really close: you just need to make one change to fix both things 
that aren't right.

- Doctor Rick, The Math Forum
  <http://mathforum.org/dr.math/>

